WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.620
Now let's talk tech. These are the tools
you'll use daily.

2
00:00:04.120 --> 00:00:08.720
Before you start making calls or sending
messages to homeowners, I want to walk you

3
00:00:08.720 --> 00:00:11.340
through the tools we use every single day.

4
00:00:12.800 --> 00:00:15.380
Understanding our tech stack is not
optional.

5
00:00:15.960 --> 00:00:21.840
These tools are how we stay organized, how we
track deals, how we communicate as a team,

6
00:00:21.980 --> 00:00:27.100
and how we grow. If you use them the right
way, they will make your job a lot easier.

7
00:00:27.240 --> 00:00:29.980
If you skip steps or try to work around
them,

8
00:00:29.980 --> 00:00:33.200
things will fall through the cracks and
deals will get lost.

9
00:00:33.500 --> 00:00:38.480
So let me walk you through each one and tell
you exactly what it does and why it matters

10
00:00:38.480 --> 00:00:39.980
here at the BMH Group.

11
00:00:41.140 --> 00:00:42.940
The first tool is Sandra.

12
00:00:43.460 --> 00:00:49.380
This is our CRM, and it is the center of
everything we do at the BMH Group.

13
00:00:49.720 --> 00:00:55.220
Every lead we generate, every homeowner we
talk to, every deal we are working lives

14
00:00:55.220 --> 00:00:59.960
inside Sandra. When you get a new lead, it
goes into Sandra.

15
00:00:59.960 --> 00:01:03.720
When you have a conversation with a
homeowner, you log notes in Sandra.

16
00:01:04.040 --> 00:01:07.640
When a deal moves from one stage to the
next, you update it in Sandra.

17
00:01:07.860 --> 00:01:11.940
Think of it as the single source of truth
for our entire operation.

18
00:01:12.500 --> 00:01:15.480
If it is not in Sandra, it does not exist.

19
00:01:16.180 --> 00:01:19.160
That is the standard we hold ourselves to
here.

20
00:01:20.260 --> 00:01:22.640
There's more to Sandra than we'll cover
today.

21
00:01:22.820 --> 00:01:27.140
When you start working with real leads, the
team will walk you through the parts that

22
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:29.240
matter for your role. For now,

23
00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:34.460
just understand, this tool is
non-negotiable.

24
00:01:35.920 --> 00:01:39.760
Next is PropStream. This is how we find
motivated sellers.

25
00:01:40.480 --> 00:01:44.260
PropStream gives us access to property data
across the country.

26
00:01:44.740 --> 00:01:47.660
We use it to pull lists of distressed
homeowners.

27
00:01:47.700 --> 00:01:53.200
That includes people who are behind on taxes,
people going through probate, properties

28
00:01:53.200 --> 00:01:56.520
with code violations, absentee owners and
more.

29
00:01:56.940 --> 00:01:59.220
When your manager gives you a list, it came

30
00:01:59.220 --> 00:02:04.680
from PropStream. It is also how we look up
property details to understand what a house

31
00:02:04.680 --> 00:02:08.420
might be worth and what kind of situation
the owner is likely in.

32
00:02:08.700 --> 00:02:12.980
If Sandra is where we manage our relationships,
then PropStream is where we find them in

33
00:02:12.980 --> 00:02:18.280
the first place. DealMachine is another tool
we use to source leads.

34
00:02:18.480 --> 00:02:23.600
Where PropStream is from your desk, DealMachine
is built around driving for dollars.

35
00:02:23.600 --> 00:02:27.560
That means going through neighborhoods and
flagging properties that look vacant,

36
00:02:27.880 --> 00:02:29.140
neglected or distressed.

37
00:02:29.140 --> 00:02:34.400
DealMachine lets you tag those properties,
pull owner information and drop them

38
00:02:34.400 --> 00:02:36.340
directly into a marketing campaign.

39
00:02:37.100 --> 00:02:41.680
For our team, this tool is part of how we
keep a steady pipeline of leads coming in.

40
00:02:41.920 --> 00:02:44.480
You need to know how it fits into our
process.

41
00:02:45.940 --> 00:02:50.280
Deal Sniper is a tool we use to generate
offers quickly and reliably.

42
00:02:50.940 --> 00:02:56.380
Speed is important. The more offers you send,
the greater your chances of transacting a

43
00:02:56.380 --> 00:02:59.120
deal. It helps us filter and evaluate
properties.

44
00:02:59.120 --> 00:03:02.940
So we can move fast when a good deal shows
up.

45
00:03:03.320 --> 00:03:05.080
In this business, speed matters.

46
00:03:05.560 --> 00:03:08.380
When a homeowner is motivated, they need to
move quickly.

47
00:03:08.820 --> 00:03:13.000
We need to be ready to make an offer without
wasting their time or ours.

48
00:03:13.400 --> 00:03:16.820
Deal Sniper helps us make confident
decisions fast.

49
00:03:17.720 --> 00:03:19.740
Now let's talk about Dialpad.

50
00:03:20.320 --> 00:03:21.540
This is our phone system.

51
00:03:22.340 --> 00:03:25.680
All outbound calls to homeowners go through
Dialpad.

52
00:03:26.280 --> 00:03:30.400
It records calls, logs your activity and
keeps everything organized.

53
00:03:30.820 --> 00:03:32.420
Your calls are being recorded.

54
00:03:33.480 --> 00:03:35.920
That is not there to watch over your
shoulder.

55
00:03:36.060 --> 00:03:39.500
It is there so we can coach you and help you
get better.

56
00:03:39.992 --> 00:03:44.135
When your manager listens to your calls and
gives you feedback, that feedback is coming

57
00:03:44.135 --> 00:03:46.095
from real conversations you had.

58
00:03:46.400 --> 00:03:51.820
Dialpad is also how we track your call volume,
how many calls you made and how long you

59
00:03:51.820 --> 00:03:53.580
were on the phone are all visible.

60
00:03:54.460 --> 00:03:57.120
Show up and make your dials.

61
00:03:57.120 --> 00:04:00.240
Closer Lab is an AI speech coaching tool.

62
00:04:00.640 --> 00:04:03.080
We use it specifically for training and
roleplay.

63
00:04:03.730 --> 00:04:07.730
Before you ever get on the phone with a real
homeowner, you are going to practice in

64
00:04:07.730 --> 00:04:09.890
Closer Lab with an AI roleplay agent.

65
00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:11.640
It listens to how you speak.

66
00:04:11.800 --> 00:04:17.840
It gives you feedback on things like filler
words, pacing, clarity and confidence.

67
00:04:18.060 --> 00:04:21.680
It lets you practice without the pressure of
a live call.

68
00:04:21.680 --> 00:04:26.720
You are going to use Closer Lab to work
through objection roleplays and call

69
00:04:26.720 --> 00:04:28.980
simulations. Take it seriously.

70
00:04:29.389 --> 00:04:30.151
Put in the reps.

71
00:04:31.620 --> 00:04:33.500
Tasks live in Sandra too.

72
00:04:33.820 --> 00:04:37.320
If your manager assigns you something, it
will be in Sandra.

73
00:04:37.680 --> 00:04:41.420
If there is a follow-up that needs to
happen, it gets logged in Sandra.

74
00:04:41.420 --> 00:04:46.600
If there is a process or a checklist to work
through, you will find it there as well.

75
00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:50.500
We use those task lists to make sure nothing
gets dropped.

76
00:04:50.940 --> 00:04:53.200
In this business, organization is
everything.

77
00:04:53.740 --> 00:04:55.400
Check your task list every day.

78
00:04:55.780 --> 00:04:57.380
Complete your tasks on time.

79
00:04:57.580 --> 00:05:01.720
If something is blocked or you need help,
flag it to your manager in Slack.

80
00:05:02.940 --> 00:05:05.060
Hubstaff is our time tracking tool.

81
00:05:05.581 --> 00:05:08.058
When you are working, you are clocked into
Hubstaff.

82
00:05:08.420 --> 00:05:10.440
It tracks your hours and activity.

83
00:05:10.580 --> 00:05:15.260
It helps us make sure you are getting paid
accurately for the hours you put in.

84
00:05:15.498 --> 00:05:16.641
Clock in when you start.

85
00:05:17.068 --> 00:05:18.211
Clock out when you stop.

86
00:05:18.660 --> 00:05:19.280
It matters.

87
00:05:20.640 --> 00:05:22.880
Slack is how we communicate as a team.

88
00:05:23.240 --> 00:05:24.860
Email is not how we operate.

89
00:05:25.380 --> 00:05:27.900
If you need to reach your manager, do it in
Slack.

90
00:05:28.260 --> 00:05:29.500
Keep notifications on.

91
00:05:29.916 --> 00:05:34.636
Slack is also where we share wins, updates,
and team announcements, so staying active

92
00:05:34.636 --> 00:05:36.351
keeps you connected to the business.

93
00:05:38.040 --> 00:05:42.640
BMH Institute is our training platform, and
it is where you are right now.

94
00:05:42.940 --> 00:05:45.080
All of your onboarding training lives here.

95
00:05:45.410 --> 00:05:47.030
Work through the modules in order.

96
00:05:47.300 --> 00:05:51.500
Each lesson builds on the one before it, and
there are quizzes to make sure the material

97
00:05:51.500 --> 00:05:54.720
is sticking. Your progress is tracked for
your manager.

98
00:05:55.860 --> 00:05:59.180
Finally, we use Google Docs for
documentation.

99
00:06:00.140 --> 00:06:05.840
SOPs, scripts, templates, and reference
materials all live here.

100
00:06:06.360 --> 00:06:07.940
Get comfortable in Google Drive.

101
00:06:08.500 --> 00:06:11.300
We share documents as you move through
onboarding.

102
00:06:11.460 --> 00:06:14.700
Bookmark the documents that are most
relevant to your daily work.

103
00:06:15.120 --> 00:06:20.440
Please ask your team lead how to locate
specific SOPs or standard operating procedures

104
00:06:20.440 --> 00:06:23.040
for the applications and tools we've
discussed.

105
00:06:24.040 --> 00:06:30.100
We covered a lot. These are the most important
tools used in the BMH Group tech stack.

106
00:06:30.440 --> 00:06:35.980
They work together to help us find deals,
manage leads, and communicate as a team.

107
00:06:36.360 --> 00:06:41.560
We invested in them because when we use them
the right way, we close more deals and

108
00:06:41.560 --> 00:06:42.880
serve homeowners better.

109
00:06:43.280 --> 00:06:46.600
Take notes, ask questions, and let's get to
work.

110
00:06:46.940 --> 00:06:49.960
Up next, we'll talk about the people behind
those leads.
